    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized data reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by heightened global presence, with particular emphasis on deterrence, power projection, and irregular warfare. Carrier strike groups (CSGs) and amphibious ready groups (ARGs) are actively deployed across the Indo-Pacific, Mediterranean, and Eastern Atlantic, with multiple CSGs operating in the South China Sea, Philippine Sea, and Eastern Mediterranean. USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) and USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) are notably involved in Project Freedom, a mission aimed at ensuring maritime security in the Strait of Hormuz, reflecting a direct response to regional threats. The Indo-Pacific remains a critical focus, with CSGs such as USS Nimitz (CVN-68), USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70), and USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) conducting deterrence operations, while ARGs like USS America (LHA-6) and USS Makin Island (LHD-8) support expeditionary readiness. High-altitude ISR platforms, including U-2 and Global Hawk aircraft, are operating over CONUS and allied territories, indicating sustained strategic reconnaissance. Maritime patrol helicopters (MH-60/64) are active in the Gulf of Mexico, East Coast, and Western Pacific, supporting counter-narcotics, counter-submarine, and regional security missions. Training activities are widespread, with notable concentrations in San Diego, Texas, and the UK, involving rotary-wing, fixed-wing, and special operations platforms. The integration of autonomous systems, such as Coast Guard sail drones in the Great Lakes, suggests an evolving approach to maritime domain awareness and irregular warfare. Overall, the data indicates a globally dispersed but strategically concentrated U.S. military posture, with CSGs and ARGs serving as key instruments of deterrence and crisis response, while ISR and maritime patrol assets enhance situational awareness and operational flexibility. The emphasis on Project Freedom and Indo-Pacific deployments underscores a prioritization of chokepoint security and regional deterrence, particularly in response to adversarial actions in critical maritime corridors.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
